reviews.review_text:
Or built to try.. This was like the movie A BRIDGE TO FAR for my V.W. Bus.
She threw a rod outside of Toledo Ohio. 
The entire crew ended up on the HOUND back to N.Y.C
 (one of the worst experiences of my entire years touring.)
But 1st we somehow managed to get to the Crisler Arena for the Second Show. Truthfully there is only one fragment of the show I still remember and that is pre-drums Scarlet>Fire , Playing >Built to Last.
That BTL made a huge impression on me.
Just by where Garcia put it in the set I could tell that he  had high hopes for the tune. (The PITB sets it up nicely here)
I know it never gelled live in the way that I sensed that Jerry wanted but I did enjoy hearing it  live especially during my road trip from hell.
